-day period for CCR\n$\\alpha_{IR}$ = $\\epsilon_{IR}$ = 0.82 was computed to be -0.59 pm/s$^2$. For\nCCR $\\alpha_{IR}$ = $\\epsilon_{IR}$ = 0.60 we compute -0.36 pm/s$^2$. Thus, our\nmodel demonstrates that most of the anomalous along-track acceleration can be\nexplained by thermal thrust, but there could be smaller contributions from\nunmodelled effects.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 19 Jul 2015 17:48:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 25 Jul 2015 22:09:52 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 13 Oct 2015 17:08:54 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 4 Mar 2016 15:09:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-07"}
